posts.subject: Yeah, but things are now worse than this....
posts.body:
And it's hard to see norms going back.

If war breaks out. it's hard to imagine journalists ever shedding the stigma of "opposing combatant".  They would be executed on the spot. No one would take the risk of letting the enemy escape.

Journalists have made their bed and have condemned their "profession" to destruction.

Practitioners were once suspected....but jury is now in. See no way they'll ever regain "protected status".

posts.body:
Case study 1.

This one reeks of "barren woman catlady" - yet she now sucks off taxpayers to ply her know nothing garbage?

How many more like her are we stuck with? Can you see there is no upside for society here? Just liabilities. This is truly a planetary alignment at it's worst. Government letting the cockroaches in.

Childless females appear to be the worst of the worse.

posts.subject: What is the truth?
posts.body:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martin_Bryant


Political aftermath

As a response to the spree killing, Australian state and territory governments placed extensive restrictions on all firearms, including semi-automatic centre-fire rifles, repeating shotguns (holding more than five shots) and high-capacity rifle magazines. In addition to this, limitations were also put into place on low-capacity repeating shotguns and rim-fire semi-automatic rifles. Though this resulted in stirring controversy, opposition to the new laws was overcome by media reporting of the massacre and mounting public opinion in the wake of the shootings (see Gun laws in Australia for more information on the 1996 legislation).

posts.subject: Hey Corporations - especially  Krispy Kreme
posts.body:
Once was a regular at McDonalds. But then that pink slime scandal hit....Found more honest suppliers - then never went back. Over 10 years now?

Feel the same way about woke virtual signalling. Will simply find other suppliers. After all, I never asked you to do *anything* - other than fill my order. Guess you couldn't get that right.

I have the vaccine. But will NEVER be your customer again. Hope many others won't either.
